          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="perg">
                
                <foliation/>
                <collation/>
                <condition>
                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>Paper, 10 in. by 6 3/4, consisting of 118 leaves, some of which are much
                        torn, especially foll. 36, 112, 113, 117, and 118. The quires, signed with
                        letters, were originally 35 in number; but there now remain only ܝܒ ــ ܒ and
                        ܠܗ ــ ܠܒ, and even some of these are very imperfect, since leaves are
                        wanting after foll. 8, 18, 26, 108, 109, 111, and 114. There are from 16 to
                        18 lines in each page. </p>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </condition>
              </supportDesc>
              
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="2">
              <handNote medium="unknown" xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr">
                <desc>This volume is written in a good, regular hand of the xiiith or xivth
                  cent.</desc>
              </handNote>
              <handNote medium="unknown" xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr">
                <desc>See additions.</desc>
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <p/>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <locus from="116a" to="118b"/>
                  <p>On foll. 116 a and 118 b there are some fragments of hymns, in different
                    hands.</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr"/>
                  </p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="117b"/>
                  <p>Foll. 117 b contains part of a canon for the Commemoration of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/624">the blessed
                    Virgin</persName> on the 15th of Iyār: </p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܬܘܒ ܩܢܘܢܐ ܕܥܠ ܩܕܝܫܬܐ ܝ̇ܠܕܬ݀ ܐܠܗܐ ܡܪܝܡ ܕܡܫܬܡܠܐ ܒܟ̣ܣܐ ܕܐܝܪ
                      ܐܝ܏ܟܘܣ ܬܡܝܢܝܐ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
            
            
